Flooding In Virginia, Update

   Description of hydrologic event:
   Rains from July 29-30, 2001 across Virginia caused flooding in the
   southwest portions of the State during Saturday night and Sunday. Minor
   flooding has occured in the Kanawha and Big Sandy River Basins.
   Moderate flooding has occurred in the Tennessee River Basin. Several
   gaging stations have exceeded the 20 year recurrence interval and are
   still rising; however, they are not expected to exceed the discharge
   associated with the 30 year recurrence interval.


