  The following information is from the National Weather Service

   Severe Weather Alert from the National Weather Service

   ...RIVER FLOOD STATEMENT NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE BLACKSBURG VA 934 AM
   EDT MON JUL 30 2001

   WATER LEVELS HAVE RECEDED TO BELOW FLOOD STAGE FOR ALL LOCATIONS FOR
   THE NORTH FORK HOLSTON RIVER.

   RUNOFF FROM THE WEEKEND RAINFALL PRODUCED A CREST AT THE SALTVILLE GAGE
   OF 11.79 FEET AT MIDNIGHT SUNDAY. THE RIVER RECEDED BELOW THE 10 FOOT
   FLOOD STAGE AROUND 5:00 AM TODAY AND IS EXPECTED TO CONTINUE FALLING.

   AT SALTVILLE, THE LATEST STAGE IS 8.0 FEET AT 9:30 AM MONDAY. NO
   ADDITIONAL FLOODING IS FORECAST.

   LISTEN TO NOAA WEATHER RADIO OR YOUR FAVORITE MEDIA OUTLET FOR LATER
   STATEMENTS OR WARNINGS.

